---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="MeetHalf ‚Äî Raman Kumar"
  description="Fair meetup location finder for groups using multi-modal routing and smart POI suggestions."
>
  <article class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <!-- Breadcrumb -->
    <div class="mb-8">
      <span class="font-mono text-sm">
        <a
          href="/"
          class="text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 hover:text-slate-900 dark:hover:text-white transition-colors"
          >~/raman-kumar</a
        >
        <span class="text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400">/</span>
        <a
          href="/projects"
          class="text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 hover:text-slate-900 dark:hover:text-white transition-colors"
          >projects</a
        >
        <span class="text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400">/</span>
        <span class="text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">meethalf</span>
      </span>
    </div>

    <!-- Header - No gradient blobs, clean solid design -->
    <header
      class="mb-12 border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-6 bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-900 border-2 border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 p-8"
    >
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 flex-wrap">
          <span
            class="px-3 py-1 text-xs font-mono uppercase bg-blue-500 text-white"
          >
            Web
          </span>
          <span class="text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
            October 2025 ‚Ä¢ Work in Progress
          </span>
        </div>

        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold">MeetHalf</h1>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 max-w-2xl">
          Smart meeting planner that finds the fairest location for groups where
          everyone has different travel modes.
        </p>

        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
          <a
            href="https://github.com/Gherra/MeetHalf"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="px-5 py-2 bg-slate-900 dark:bg-white text-white dark:text-slate-900 font-medium border-2 border-slate-900 dark:border-white hover:bg-white dark:hover:bg-slate-900 hover:text-slate-900 dark:hover:text-white transition-colors"
          >
            View Code
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <!-- Stats Grid -->
    <section class="mb-8 grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-4">
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div
          class="text-xs font-mono uppercase text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 mb-1"
        >
          People
        </div>
        <div class="text-xl font-bold">2‚Äì8+</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div
          class="text-xs font-mono uppercase text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 mb-1"
        >
          Modes
        </div>
        <div class="text-sm font-semibold">Car ‚Ä¢ Transit ‚Ä¢ Walk</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div
          class="text-xs font-mono uppercase text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 mb-1"
        >
          Goal
        </div>
        <div class="text-sm font-semibold">Min Avg Time</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div
          class="text-xs font-mono uppercase text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 mb-1"
        >
          Status
        </div>
        <div class="text-sm font-semibold">WIP</div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Screenshots -->
    <section class="mb-8 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <div
        class="border-2 border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 overflow-hidden"
      >
        <img
          src="/images/meethalf-1.png"
          alt="Participants & modes"
          class="w-full h-auto"
        />
      </div>
      <div
        class="border-2 border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 overflow-hidden"
      >
        <img
          src="/images/meethalf-2.png"
          alt="Map with venue options"
          class="w-full h-auto"
        />
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Caption -->
    <p
      class="mb-12 text-sm text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 border-l-2 border-slate-300 dark:border-slate-700 pl-4"
    >
      <strong class="text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">Left:</strong> Participant
      setup with multi-modal travel options.
      <strong class="text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">Right:</strong> Ranked meeting
      spots with per-person travel times.
    </p>

    <!-- At a Glance -->
    <section class="mb-8 card p-6 border-l-4 border-blue-500">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">Overview</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 text-sm">
        <li>
          <strong class="text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">Problem:</strong> Fairly
          choosing meetup spots for 2‚Äì8+ people with different travel modes.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong class="text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">Solution:</strong> Route-aware
          algorithm that minimizes group average travel time using Google Maps APIs.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Main Content -->
    <div
      class="card prose prose-slate dark:prose-invert max-w-none
            prose-headings:scroll-mt-24
            prose-h2:text-2xl prose-h2:font-bold prose-h2:mt-10 prose-h2:mb-4
            prose-h3:text-lg prose-h3:font-semibold prose-h3:mt-6 prose-h3:mb-3
            prose-p:text-slate-700 dark:prose-p:text-slate-300
            prose-p:leading-relaxed
            prose-a:text-blue-600 dark:prose-a:text-blue-400 hover:prose-a:underline
            prose-strong:text-slate-900 dark:prose-strong:text-slate-100
            px-6 py-8"
    >
      <h2>Problem & Motivation</h2>
      <p>
        Existing apps like MeetWays and Midpointr are great for 2 people, but
        fail when you need to coordinate groups:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Limited to 2-3 people</li>
        <li>
          Force everyone to use the same travel mode (everyone drives OR
          everyone uses transit)
        </li>
        <li>Don't show per-person travel times for each venue suggestion</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        <strong>MeetHalf solves all of these.</strong> It supports 2-8+ people, lets
        each person choose their own travel mode (driving üöó, transit üöá, or walking
        üö∂), and shows exact travel times for everyone at each suggested venue.
      </p>

      <h2>How It Works</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>
          <strong>Add participants:</strong> Enter names, addresses (with Google
          autocomplete), and preferred travel modes
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Choose venue type:</strong> Caf√©, restaurant, library, or park
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Get smart suggestions:</strong> Algorithm finds top 5 places optimized
          for fairness
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Compare options:</strong> See travel time breakdown for each person
          at each venue
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Navigate:</strong> Click "Open in Google Maps" to get directions
        </li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Technical Stack</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Next.js 15:</strong> React framework with server-side rendering
        </li>
        <li><strong>TypeScript:</strong> Type-safe development</li>
        <li><strong>Tailwind CSS:</strong> Utility-first styling</li>
        <li>
          <strong>Google Maps Platform:</strong> Maps JavaScript API, Places API,
          Directions API, Geocoding API
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Links</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://github.com/Gherra/MeetHalf"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >
            GitHub Repository
          </a>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Navigation -->
    <nav
      class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t-2 border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 grid grid-cols-3 text-sm"
    >
      <a
        href="/projects/moviefinder"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 hover:text-slate-600 dark:hover:text-slate-400"
      >
        <span>‚Üê</span> MovieFinder
      </a>

      <a
        href="/"
        class="mx-auto hover:text-slate-600 dark:hover:text-slate-400"
      >
        Home
      </a>

      <a
        href="/projects/panorama-fastr-stitch"
        class="justify-self-end inline-flex items-center gap-2 hover:text-slate-600 dark:hover:text-slate-400"
      >
        Panorama <span>‚Üí</span>
      </a>
    </nav>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
